2026-06-15  Arc 5 item 12.5 redo (can't-lie): optimistic co-assignees rebuilt — the pane list is hook-owned (keyed <ul> + phx-update=ignore, no morphdom fight); each add/remove/reorder snapshots the list, applies it, then pushes the event WITH A REPLY and reverts the snapshot on {ok:false} or an 8s timeout. with_co now replies {ok:bool}. A write that doesn't land snaps back instead of sticking. (Pending browser re-test.)
2026-06-15  Arc 5 item 12.6.2: Viewer+ direct-assignee grant — a global viewer who is a task's primary assignee may now move progress and post comments on that task and its whole subtree. Server gates (set_progress, toggle_complete, request_cascade, add_comment, update_task) and UI surfaces (done-toggle, slider, comment form) check can_progress? = can_edit OR leads this task; led set comes from the recursive-CTE viewer_plus_led_ids, refreshed with the tree. update_task takes only manual_progress for a lead (defense-in-depth). Titles/priority/structure/staffing stay can_edit. Behavior tests land under 12.6.6.
2026-06-15  Arc 5 items 12.6.3/12.6.4: Viewer+ staffing — a lead may set a *descendant's* primary and co-assignees, drawn only from the people they were handed (the nearest led ancestor's co-assignees; Tasks.viewer_staff_pool). The editor's assignee select + co-add dropdown list only that pool (plus the current primary, so it reads true); both are absent/disabled where the viewer holds no lead. Server enforces: update_task takes a pool-valid assignee_id, add_co_assignee refuses out-of-pool (reply ok:false → optimistic row reverts). The led task's own co-list and titles/priority stay owner/editor-only. Tests: viewer_staff_pool pool + nearest-ancestor shrink.
2026-06-15  Arc 5 items 12.6.5/12.6.6: Viewer+ label + tests — a viewer who is a direct assignee somewhere now reads "viewer+" in the members panel (owners keep the editable select + a small badge; everyone else sees the role text flip; DB role stays viewer). Set is derived in-memory from the loaded tree, no extra query. Tests: LiveView walkthrough (grant on the led subtree, read-only outside, pool-only staffing for assignee + co, out-of-pool add refused, led task's own co-list/title off-limits, the label, off-setting = no grant). Item 12.6 (Viewer+) complete.
2026-06-15  Arc 5 item 12.7: the "← All initiatives" back link is now a "Close Initiative" control with a little red X (matching the task pane's close affordance); still navigates to the index.
2026-06-15  Arc 5 item 12.8: drag a member onto a task to assign — Members-panel avatars gain a vertical-ellipsis drag handle (shown only when the current user can assign); a MemberDrag pointer hook highlights the task row (indigo ring) and on drop pushes assign_member. Server assigns the member as PRIMARY when the task has none, else stacks them as a CO — never clobbering the primary (already-assigned = no-op). Validated per the dropped task: editor/owner anywhere, viewer+ only within a led subtree from its pool; illegal drops are a no-op + flash. Honest optimism: the row shows the saving hue in-flight, the chip lands on the patch. Assignee select / co-list stay the a11y + touch path. Tests cover the assign_member outcomes.
2026-06-15  Arc 6 item 1 + soft-delete foundation: tasks gain deleted_at (soft-delete) and activity_events gain inverse_payload (undo reversal data). delete_task now soft-deletes the whole subtree (id, comments, co-assignees, descendants preserved) and records child_deleted with the deleted ids in inverse_payload; restore_tasks clears the flag and reloads. All task reads filter deleted_at IS NULL. Resolves the delete-reversibility Open Question (operator chose soft-delete over re-insert/new-id).
2026-06-15  Arc 6 items 2/3 (+7/8 engine-level): undo/redo engine. Tasks.undo/2 + redo/2 reverse a user's own newest undoable event on an Initiative (move, reorder, delete, create, title/progress/priority/assignee), stepping over other members' edits. Per-(user,Initiative) stack derived from a new undone_at on events (persists across reconnect); a fresh action invalidates redo. Non-delete inverses read the events' from/to; delete/create use the soft-delete flag; moves capture the prior slot in inverse_payload. Conflicts (e.g. inverse parent gone) surface gracefully and skip the dead entry; undid/redid meta events recorded for the feed. validate_move now rejects a soft-deleted parent.
2026-06-15  Arc 6 items 4-9: undo/redo UI. Undo/Redo buttons in the Initiative header (disabled when the stack is empty that way; tooltip names the action); Ctrl/Cmd+Z = undo, +Shift or Ctrl+Y = redo via the tree key listener (suppressed in fields so native undo works). Handlers reverse/re-apply and flash the outcome (incl. friendly conflict + nothing-to-undo messages). Bounded to the 50 most recent undoable events per user/Initiative. undid/redid entries show in the activity feed. Undo state refreshed wherever the tree is. Tests: toolbar availability + handler round-trip + empty-stack flash.
2026-06-15  Arc 6 items 10/11: Initiative Trash. Deleting an Initiative now soft-deletes it (initiatives.trashed_at) — it leaves every member's dashboard but is restorable. The index shows an owner-only Trash section (Restore + permanent Delete); list_visible_initiatives filters trashed. Retention: trashed Initiatives auto-purge after 30 days (config), swept lazily on index mount; owner can purge sooner. delete_initiative split into trash_initiative / restore_initiative / purge_initiative. (Item 12 account-deletion handoff deferred — owner_id is on_delete:restrict, needs an ownership decision.)
