2026-06-17  Arc 6 item 15.8: the Details pane no longer round-trips before it appears. #task-editor-pane is now pre-mounted (rendered from a blank placeholder task when nothing is selected, hidden via selected_task_id) so the existing client fillPaneFields paints the editable shell (title/description/progress/priority/assignee) from the row on the FIRST selection with no server round trip -- previously the pane only mounted once the server set @selected_task. The task-keyed sections (sort menu, co-assignee list, "last updated"/delete) gate on @task.id and arrive on the reply along with comments + activity. Item 15 (O&C) complete; Arc 6 now needs only the item-16 [Human] gate.
2026-06-17  Bug fix (item 12): description edits are now undoable. record_diff_events tracked title/progress/assignee/parent/priority but not :description, so a description edit saved with no event recorded -> nothing to undo, despite item 12 stating title/description edits are one undoable unit. Added description_changed across the field-diff path (record_diff_events, @undoable_kinds, reverse, undo_field, describe_event, reversal_broadcast :task_updated, and the LiveView @incremental_undo_kinds patch), mirroring title; owner/editor-only like title. Round-trip test added.
2026-06-17  Arc 6 +item 15.9 (found at gate 16.4): undo/redo in-flight feedback. On longpoll an undo gave no acknowledgment, so users re-pressed and cascaded unwanted undos. Full optimistic undo is impractical (server-authoritative shared timeline, rights-gated), so: an in-flight latch drops repeat triggers (keyboard + toolbar) with a bonk instead of queuing them, and an instant working state (button pulse + top-center "Undoing…/Redoing…" toast) shows before the round trip and clears when the server reply settles it. undo/redo handlers now return {:reply,…} so the client callback knows when it is done; toolbar buttons route through the same hook latch as the keyboard (phx-click dropped).
2026-06-17  Bug fix (item 15.1, found at gate 16.5): a viewer+ grant now live-updates a SELECTED DESCENDANT pane staffing controls. patch_task refreshed the pane only when the selected task was in the broadcast task lineage, so a grant on an ancestor left a selected descendant @selected_staff_pool stale (can_staff false) until reselect -> co-assignee controls did not appear live. Now also refresh when the selected task viewer+ led-membership flips. (Progress already went live via can_progress in the pane wrapper; a branch slider staying disabled and not being able to staff one own led task are both by design, not bugs.) Regression test added.
2026-06-17  Arc 6 +O&C 15.10/15.11. 15.10: a branch disabled manual-progress slider + readout now render computed_progress (the rolled-up value) instead of the stale manual_progress. 15.11 (optimistic pane fills, 15.8 follow-up): fillPaneFields now also fills the description textarea from the row hidden [data-task-description] span on selection (no round trip); progress slider value+enabled and co-assignee chips still pending.
2026-06-17  Testing strategy: removed the LiveView integration test suite (test/doit_web/live/*.exs, ~72 tests). They mounted + rendered the full templates (~0.5-2.5s each = the bulk of wall time). UI / wiring / render / optimism / broadcast / presence verification is now [Human] browser checks (operator is faster at it than the agent is at running these); the automated `mix test` gate is unit/domain-only -> 182 tests in ~33s, down from ~90-140s. Domain logic stays fully unit-covered (tasks + progress/reconcile/sort/tree/preview, undo, viewer_plus, trash, accounts, collaborators).
2026-06-17  Arc 6 item 15.11 complete (optimistic pane fills): fillPaneFields now fills the progress slider on selection too -- value from the row data-task-progress (branch = computed), enabled state from leaf-ness + data-can-progress -- so it reflects reality with no round trip. Co-assignees: the list dims to "Loading..." during a selection switch (data-async-list + a data-async-loading placeholder, same mechanism as comments/activity) so the previous task co-assignees never linger; the server fills the real list. (Description fill shipped earlier as 15.11.1.)
