2026-07-03  Feat (m03.03): item 2.1 -- POST /api/v1/operations (and its MCP mirror apply_operations) now caps a batch at 150 ops, rejected up front with a 422 naming the count + limit before any DB work, guarding the batch's single synchronous transaction against the 15 s timeout. Benchmark-backed (~40-55 ms/op cascade-heavy; ~2x headroom).
2026-07-03  Feat (m03.03): item 2.2 -- POST /api/v1/operations honors a client-supplied Idempotency-Key header (Stripe-style): first attempt executes and its response is stored per (user, key) for 24h; a retry with the same key replays that stored response instead of re-applying the batch, so a client-side timeout can't double-apply. New api_idempotency_keys table; apply_operations MCP tool forwards an optional idempotency_key. Only execution outcomes are stored (pre-exec rejections aren't).
2026-07-06  Feat (m03.03): item 3 -- %-notation task cross-reference UI. Typing % + a task's dotted number in a title / description / comment / chat / Initiative name-subtitle-description creates a link resolved at entry (label -> stable id) and rendered with the target's LIVE current number, clickable to select + scroll; a "Link task" picker inserts refs at the cursor, edit mode rehydrates tokens back to %label (never the id), and \% escapes a literal. Title/description also write a task_links edge (feeding the API's cross_references); comments, chat, and Initiative fields are inline-token only. Dashboard list-cards render a neutral ↗ glyph (no tree loaded to resolve there). Save-confirm (item 3.5, client-side per UX_GUARDRAILS 6.5): a blur/submit that resolves a NEW ref set HOLDS the save and opens a confirm listing each ref's label + title before commit -- Proceed commits, Cancel returns to the field with the edit intact; fires only when the ref set changed since the last commit; skip-again persists in localStorage; chat is exempt. Fields commit via a single-field pushEvent on Proceed (a programmatic blur doesn't re-drive LiveView's debounce flush), comment add rides DoitPush, comment edit resumes via requestSubmit. Also fixed a latent multi-ref-field flush that re-saved a sibling field's rehydrated %label as literal, destroying its stored token. Verified against the live stack with the DB as ground truth. 458 tests green.
2026-07-06  Fix (m03.03): item 3 follow-ups. (1) Cut %-notation from the Initiative Name -- it renders inside the header's click-to-edit button, where a nested ref link fights the edit affordance; Name reverts to plain text (phx-debounce 600, no RefField/picker/marker). Subtitle + Description keep refs. (2) Escapes now resolve in RENDERED ref-LESS text: renderRefEl/renderCardRefEl early-returned when an element held no linkable ref, so a \% or \\ with no ref nearby stayed raw (\% showed as \% instead of %, \\ as \\); ref-less text now still resolves \%->% and \\->\ at render time, matching item 3.1.4 (edit boxes keep the escapes verbatim).
2026-07-06  Change (m03.03): item 3.5 -- replaced the blocking save-confirm with a non-blocking toast. A title/description/comment (and Initiative subtitle/description) save is now OPTIMISTIC and never held; when it resolves a NEW/changed %-ref set, a self-dismissing "Linked <label> — <title>, ..." toast reports what got linked, so a valid-but-wrong target stays visible without gating every valid ref. Fires only on a changed set (unchanged re-save is silent); chat + Initiative Name exempt. Removes the #ref-confirm modal, the skip-again, and all the hold/pushEvent/requestSubmit commit machinery -- the save reverts to the original native-flush / DoitPush path (tokenizeSiblings retained so a sibling ref field isn't re-saved as literal %label). Operator's call: valid-but-correct-until-proven-guilty.
2026-07-06  Change (m03.03): item 3.5 -- moved the "Linked …" notification onto the app's canonical flash (put_flash), retiring the first-pass client-side toast (a separate toast system, per operator feedback). The save handlers (update_task, update_subtitle, update_initiative, add_comment, save_comment) now diff the resolved %-ref set server-side (Tasks.reference_ids/1) and, when it changed + is non-empty, put_flash(:info, "Linked <label> — <title>, …") through the existing toast/AutoDismissFlash -- ONE toast system, and the firing diff moves to the server (which has old+new). Labels+titles resolve off the loaded :tree via the new Tasks.label_index/2 (unified: the API serializer's private build_label_index moved into the Tasks context, one walk shared by cross_references + the flash); tokens stripped from titles (Tasks.strip_reference_tokens/1) so the raw id never shows. Removed all the client toast/firing code (showRefToast, maybeToastRefs, committedRefKey, refDetails). Verified against the live stack: a comment save with a new ref renders "Linked 1 — M19 …". 458 tests green.
